The paper discusses channel estimation in massive MIMO systems, which involves signal processing, wireless communication, and statistical inference. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the fundamental limits of communication and information processing. The paper also involves network infrastructure (base stations), which suggests the sub-category cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The use of spatial multiplexing and interference suppression techniques indicates the sub-category cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper specifically focuses on the performance comparison of different channel estimation methods, which falls under the sub-category cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the use of Bayesian inference and prior distributions suggests the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning).
